Package: intp
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 libintp1 (= ${binary:Version}),
Description: Linux interference profiler
 intp measures cross-workload performance interference on Linux hosts.
 It collects seven metrics — netp, nets, blk, mbw, llcmr, llcocc, cpu —
 that together quantify how co-located workloads compete for CPU,
 last-level cache, memory bandwidth, block I/O, and network resources.
 .
 This package contains the intp(1) command-line tool. The shared
 library is in libintp1; development headers are in libintp-dev.

Package: libintp1
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Pre-Depends: ${misc:Pre-Depends}
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
Description: Linux interference profiler — shared library
 intp measures cross-workload performance interference on Linux hosts.
 .
 This package contains the libintp.so shared library used by the
 intp(1) tool and by programs linking against the libintp public C API.

Package: libintp-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: same
Depends:
 libintp1 (= ${binary:Version}),
 ${misc:Depends},
Description: Linux interference profiler — development files
 intp measures cross-workload performance interference on Linux hosts.
 .
 This package contains the headers, pkg-config file, and other
 resources needed to develop programs that link against libintp.

Package: intp-doc
Section: doc
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Linux interference profiler — documentation
 Documentation for intp, the Linux interference profiler. Includes
 the architecture overview, metric definitions, plugin author guide,
 integration cookbook, and packaging notes.

Package: intp-plugin-bpftrace
Architecture: any
Depends:
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
 intp (= ${binary:Version}),
 libintp1 (= ${binary:Version}),
 bpftrace,
Description: Linux interference profiler — bpftrace research plugin
 Loads user-supplied bpftrace (.bt) scripts and publishes their output
 as intp plugin-defined metrics. Useful for prototyping new probes
 before promoting them to native eBPF or pure-C in-tree backends, and
 as a lighter-weight alternative on hosts where the libbpf+clang
 toolchain is unavailable.
 .
 This is a research/experimental plugin; not part of the default
 install. See /usr/share/doc/intp-doc/PLUGINS.md for usage.
